---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="SS Developers | Cape Town Web Developer for Websites, Apps, and Software" description="I build websites, web apps, and software systems for teams that need clear state, solid performance, and dependable technical ownership.">
  <section class="hero-section">
    <div class="container hero-layout">
      <div class="hero-text stack-lg" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 40ms;">
        <div class="hero-kicker">
          <span class="hero-kicker-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span>Open for focused work</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="hero-title">I build <span class="accent">websites, web apps, and software systems</span> that stay clear under pressure.</h1>
        <p class="hero-copy">
          I take on products that need more than a clean surface.
          The interface has to make sense.
          The state underneath it has to stay correct.
          I build both with care, from public sites to internal tools to systems where trust breaks fast when the data goes stale or the logic slips.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a href="/projects" class="button-primary">See my work</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="button-secondary">Start Your Project</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-visual" aria-hidden="true" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 120ms;">
        <img src="/images/redesign/hero-system-surface-wide.png" alt="" class="hero-image" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container content-split">
      <div class="visual-panel visual-panel-light" data-reveal>
        <img
          src="/images/redesign/exercise-app-tablet-light.png"
          alt="Product dashboard interface shown on a tablet."
          class="visual-panel-image visual-panel-image-contain"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="section-panel" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 60ms;">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div class="page-intro">How the work starts</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">App builds that stay fast, legible, and <span class="accent">easy to trust.</span></h2>
        </div>
        <p class="section-copy">
          I start with the parts that fail first. State. Handoffs. Load paths. Slow screens. If the product feels calm, it is because I did that work before I polished the UI.
        </p>
        <div class="feature-list">
          <div class="feature-list-item">
            <strong>Scope before screens.</strong>
            <p>I map the states, inputs, and handoffs first so the build solves the actual operating problem.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-list-item">
            <strong>Working software early.</strong>
            <p>I put the useful path in front of you early so feedback lands on real behavior, not guesses.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-list-item">
            <strong>Performance with intent.</strong>
            <p>I watch response time, rendering cost, and state churn so the product holds up on real devices once people start using it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <a href="/how-i-work" class="link-inline">See how the work runs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section timeline-tree">
    <div class="container content-split timeline-tree-layout">
      <div class="timeline-list">
        <article class="timeline-card" data-reveal>
          <strong>Websites and product apps</strong>
          <p>I build public-facing products that explain themselves fast and still hold up once the logic gets deeper.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="timeline-card" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 40ms;">
          <strong>Internal tools and system work</strong>
          <p>I build operational software for teams that need clear state, fewer manual gaps, and less guesswork.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="timeline-card" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 80ms;">
          <strong>Trading systems and fintech</strong>
          <p>I take on builds where reconciliation, execution state, contributions, payouts, or other trust-heavy flows need more care.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="timeline-card" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 120ms;">
          <strong>Product reliability and ownership</strong>
          <p>I harden the logic, interface, and handoff path so the product stays readable after launch.</p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="visual-panel" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 80ms;">
        <img
          src="/images/redesign/teacher-tracking-tool-tablet.png"
          alt="Operational dashboard shown on a tablet."
          class="visual-panel-image"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section selected-work" id="work">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head section-head--center" data-reveal>
        <div class="page-intro">Selected work</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Two builds with real <span class="accent">engineering weight.</span></h2>
        <p class="section-copy">
          One system keeps several runtimes in sync. The other keeps community finance legible for the people who rely on it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-stack">
        <article class="feature-panel" data-reveal>
          <div class="feature-panel-header">
            <div class="stack-lg">
              <div class="eyeline">Trading infrastructure</div>
              <h3 class="feature-title">SMC SuperFIB</h3>
              <p class="panel-copy">
                A cross-runtime trading system that keeps indicator logic, API state, execution clients, and operator visibility aligned.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="project-challenge">I had to keep multiple runtimes in agreement without forcing the operator to read raw logs to understand the system state.</p>
          <a href="/projects/superfib" class="link-inline">Read the SuperFIB case study</a>
        </article>

        <article class="feature-panel" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 70ms;">
          <div class="feature-panel-header">
            <div class="stack-lg">
              <div class="eyeline">Community finance</div>
              <h3 class="feature-title">Stokvel Society</h3>
              <p class="panel-copy">
                A fintech product for contributions, ledger visibility, and payout flows that members can follow without confusion.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="project-challenge">I turned a trust-heavy community finance workflow into software that keeps balances, history, and payouts easy to read.</p>
          <a href="/projects/stokvel" class="link-inline">Read the Stokvel Society case study</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section next-step" id="contact">
    <div class="container next-step-shell">
      <div class="section-panel next-step-copy" data-reveal>
        <div class="page-intro">Next step</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Read the work, then decide if the <span class="accent">fit is there.</span></h2>
        <p class="section-copy">
          The case studies show how I scope risk, design state, and carry a build through launch. You can judge the fit from the work itself.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="next-step-actions" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 60ms;">
        <a href="/projects" class="button-primary">See my work</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="button-secondary">Start Your Project</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
